  schema:name "Yin Deficiency" ;
  schema:description "阴虚 (yin xu) — the depletion of the body's cooling, moistening, anchoring substance, producing heat signs from insufficient cooling rather than excess heat — night sweats, dry mouth, five-palm heat, and a thin rapid pulse" ;
